                <p>Albert Einstein, the iconic physicist, revolutionized our understanding of the universe with his theories of relativity. Born in 1879 in Germany, he moved to the U.S. where he became a symbol of genius. His groundbreaking work laid the foundation for modern physics, and his famous equation, E=mcÂ², transformed our concept of energy and mass.</p>
